description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting development opportunity exists for a motivated individual to join the Health Education England (HEE) Training Programme Management Function as a National Recruitment Assistant, based in the North West but recruiting to a number of specialties on behalf of HEE for England, Scotland, Wales and in some cases Northern Ireland.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, effective and highly motivated individual to support colleagues in the recruitment team, to help provide administrative support for national recruitment to a number of medical and dental specialties within national deadlines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need experience of working under pressure, to set deadlines, meticulous attention to detail and be confident working with Microsoft Office packages, particularly Excel and Outlook. Experience of using online platforms, particularly MS Teams, would be advantageous.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be a confident and effective communicator, able to interact with staff at all levels. You will ideally have experience of working in the field of postgraduate medical and dental education, and/or recruitment/event management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In time, you may be expected to travel across the North West on a regular basis, attending all day recruitment events and working with staff who are primarily based in Central Manchester but may also be on our Liverpool office site on occasion. For 2021, it is likely that all specialty recruitment will take place online so you are not likely to be expected to travel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants will commence at the bottom of Band 3 with a full-time starting salary of £19,737 with a pay step increase after 2 years’ service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These salaries are offered in accordance with NHS Terms and Conditions and the HEE Pay Progression Policy and are subject to annual cost of living review.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you like what you have read and think you have the skills and experience we need then don&#39;t delay, apply today! We get lots of applications for our roles and so we sometimes have to close our posts early. Don&#39;t miss out! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Amelia O&#39;Donnell&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;0161 268 9508&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Paul Grocott&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;0161 268 9656.&lt;/p&gt;
